Looking at this proof goal, I need to show that `wignerMatrixEntryFunction ω i j = wignerMatrixEntryFunction ω j i`. The function uses nested `if` statements to handle three cases: diagonal (i = j), upper triangular (i < j), and lower triangular (j < i).

The key insight is that when we swap i and j:
- If i = j (diagonal), then j = i (still diagonal) - same element
- If i < j (upper), then j > i (lower) - accesses ⟨(i,j), _⟩ vs ⟨(i,j), _⟩ 
- If i > j (lower), then j < i (upper) - accesses ⟨(j,i), _⟩ vs ⟨(j,i), _⟩

The proof needs to case split and show equality in each branch.

```lean
lemma wignerMatrixEntryFunctionSymmetric (ω : WignerSpace n) {i : Fin n} {j : Fin n} :
  wignerMatrixEntryFunction ω i j = wignerMatrixEntryFunction ω j i := by
  rw[wignerMatrixEntryFunction, wignerMatrixEntryFunction]
  split_ifs <;> try rfl
  · subst_vars; rfl
  · omega
```
